Has anyone considered using XML for storing NN definitions? I only ask 
as I work a lot with XML for my day job and it would seem sensible for 
all the various NEAT projects to have some kind of standard for 
transfering data. The same principle also applies to genome and genome 
populations.

As an example below is some XML dumped from my previous EANN project, 
there is no DTD or XSD definition at the moment but they&#39;re easy enough 
to put together and could serve as a sort of NEAT information 
interchange standard. I find XML a nice &#39;language&#39; to use because it is 
easily readable to both humans and computers...

Colin

